        Example statement (text/turtle): <https://www.purl.org/SomeOntology> vann:preferredNamespacePrefix "so"^^xsd:string .
        """@en ;
        sh:description "This shape checks whether the ontology's preferred namespace prefix or acronym is an xsd:string. It will produce an info message if it is not."@en ;
        sh:name "Preferred prefix/ acronym datatype"@en ;
    ] ;

## Ontology license
### G-Doc https://docs.google.com/document/d/1FRmCQ7eD6PcqSQgPbqCGjki3t39ROoYozsehCPX9E0Q/edit#bookmark=id.d63b5oqb03v
### status: discuss
### Der TS nimmt die Lizenz-IRI, aber gern auch ein Label - darüber hatten wir noch nicht gesprochen
    sh:property [
        sh:path [sh:alternativePath (dcterms:license dcterms:rights schema:license cc:license dbo:license)] ;
        sh:severity sh:Warning ;
        sh:minCount 1;
        # tbd/todo: specify a list of accepted licenses? e.g. from open definition
        sh:message """The ontology does not specify its license. 
        The license should be open. Read more about open licenses at https://opendefinition.org/licenses/.
        Recommended property: <https://purl.org/dc/terms/license>
        Example statement (text/turtle): <https://www.purl.org/SomeOntology> dcterms:license <http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/> .
        """@en ;
        sh:description "This shape checks whether the ontology provides license information. The license should be provided as an IRI (https://www.w3.org/TR/rdf11-concepts/#dfn-iri), not as a Literal. The license should be open (see more at https://opendefinition.org/licenses/)."@en ;
        sh:name "License"@en ;
    ] ;

    sh:property [
        sh:path [sh:alternativePath (dcterms:license dcterms:rights schema:license cc:license dbo:license)] ;
        sh:severity sh:Info ;
        sh:or (
            [sh:nodeKind sh:IRI ;]
            [sh:datatype xsd:anyURI ;]
        ) ;
        sh:message """The ontology license is not provided as an IRI or not typed as an xsd:anyURI. Do not provide the license as an xsd:string. 
        Recommended property: <https://purl.org/dc/terms/license>
        Example statement 1 (text/turtle): <https://www.purl.org/SomeOntology> dcterms:license <http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/> .
        Example statement 2 (text/turtle): <https://www.purl.org/SomeOntology> dcterms:license "http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/"^^xsd:anyURI .
        The license should be open. Read more about open licenses at https://opendefinition.org/licenses/.
        """@en ;
        sh:description "This shape checks whether the ontology provides license information as an IRI or gives it the datatype xsd:anyURI. It will produce an info message if not."@en ;
        sh:name "License datatype"@en ;
    ] ;


## Ontology creator
### G-Doc https://docs.google.com/document/d/1FRmCQ7eD6PcqSQgPbqCGjki3t39ROoYozsehCPX9E0Q/edit#bookmark=id.uc5cfjvqg7cv
### status: discuss
### Über regex-Prüfungen könnte man hier auch bestimmte Identifier enforcen
### man könnte hier auch die Erfüllung einer shape fordern: PID als entity, name der entity als annotation dieser entity statt direkt als annotation an der ontologie
    sh:property [
        sh:path  [sh:alternativePath (dc:creator dcterms:creator schema:creator pav:createdBy prov:wasAttributedTo schema:accountablePerson schema:author)];
        sh:severity sh:Warning ;
        sh:minCount 1;
        sh:message """The ontology does not state its creator. 
        The ontology should at least name one person who was involved in developing the ontology.
        Creators should be referenced via PIDs, e.g. ORCiDs for persons and RORs for organisations.
        If an ontology is developed by a larger group, it is recommended to give the organization or project identifier as the creator and list individual persons as contributors.
        Recommended property: <https://purl.org/dc/terms/creator>
        Example statement (text/turtle): <https://www.purl.org/SomeOntology> <https://purl.org/dc/terms/creator> <https://orcid.org/0000-0000-0000-0000>.

        Plain name strings could be provided in addition (for readability).
        Example statements 2 (text/turtle): 
            <https://www.purl.org/SomeOntology> <https://purl.org/dc/terms/creator> <https://orcid.org/0000-0000-0000-0000>.
            <https://orcid.org/0000-0000-0000-0000> <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/firstName> "Max" ;
                <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/lastName> "Muster" .
        """@en ;
        sh:description "This shape checks whether the ontology provides information about its creator. It will produce a warning message if no creator information is present."@en ;
        sh:name "Creator(s)"@en ;
    ] ;

    sh:property [
        sh:path  [sh:alternativePath (dc:creator dcterms:creator schema:creator pav:createdBy prov:wasAttributedTo schema:accountablePerson schema:author)];
        sh:severity sh:Info ;
        sh:nodeKind sh:IRI;
        sh:message """The creator information provided is not an IRI.
        Please make sure to provide identifiers wherever possible.
        Creators should be referenced via PIDs, e.g. ORCiDs for persons and RORs for organisations.
        Plain name strings should only be provided in addition (for readability).
        If an ontology is developed by a larger group, it is recommended to give the organization or project identifier as the creator and list individual persons as contributors.
        Recommended property: <https://purl.org/dc/terms/creator>
        Example statement (text/turtle): <https://www.purl.org/SomeOntology> <https://purl.org/dc/terms/creator> <https://orcid.org/0000-0000-0000-0000>.
        """@en ;
        sh:description "This shape checks whether the ontology states its creator as an IRI. It will produce an info message if creator information is given e.g. as xsd:string"@en ;
        sh:name "Creator(s)"@en ;
    ] ;

## Version information
### G-Doc https://docs.google.com/document/d/1FRmCQ7eD6PcqSQgPbqCGjki3t39ROoYozsehCPX9E0Q/edit#bookmark=id.88o633ocogle

### Version IRI
#### G-Doc https://docs.google.com/document/d/1FRmCQ7eD6PcqSQgPbqCGjki3t39ROoYozsehCPX9E0Q/edit#bookmark=id.5o62yvmk2eo1
### status: discuss
    sh:property [
        sh:path  owl:versionIRI ;
        sh:severity sh:Warning ;
        sh:minCount 1 ;
        sh:maxCount 1 ;
        sh:message """The ontology does not state exactly one versionIRI. 
                 The versionIRI should be stable and resolvable, i.e. a fixed version of the ontology should be retrievable from the provided IRI.
                 It is recommended to use semantic versioning (cf. https://semver.org/) or OBO style date-based versioning (http://obofoundry.org/principles/fp-004-versioning.html).
                 Recommended property: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionIRI>
                 Example statement 1 (text/turtle): <https://www.purl.org/SomeOntology> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionIRI> <https://www.purl.org/SomeOntology/1.0.0>.
                 Example statement 2 (text/turtle): <https://www.purl.org/SomeOntology> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionIRI> <https://www.purl.org/SomeOntology/YYYY-MM-DD> .
                 Example statement 3 (text/turtle): <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/pco.owl> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionIRI> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/pco/releases/2021-05-03/pco.owl> .
                 """@en ;
        sh:description "This shape checks whether the ontology provids exactly one versionIRI. It produces a warning message if none is found."@en ;
        sh:name "Version IRI"@en ;
    ] ;

    sh:property [
        sh:path  owl:versionIRI ;
        sh:severity sh:Info ;
        sh:nodeKind sh:IRI;
        sh:message """The ontology does not state the versionIRI as an IRI. It should not be given as a sring or literal.
                 Recommended property: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionIRI>
                 Example statement (text/turtle): <https://www.purl.org/SomeOntology> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionIRI> <https://www.purl.org/SomeOntology/1.0.0>.
                 """@en ;
        sh:description "This shape checks whether the ontology versionIRI is provided as an IRI (https://www.w3.org/TR/rdf11-concepts/#dfn-iri) (as compared to a literal). It produces an info message if it is not."@en ;
        sh:name "Version IRI datatype"@en ;
    ] ;

### Creation date
#### G-Doc https://docs.google.com/document/d/1FRmCQ7eD6PcqSQgPbqCGjki3t39ROoYozsehCPX9E0Q/edit#bookmark=id.7i4grrp5qlng
### status: final
    sh:property [
        sh:path [sh:alternativePath (dcterms:created schema:dateCreated pav:createdOn prov:generatedAtTime )] ;
        sh:severity sh:Warning ;
        sh:minCount 1;
        sh:maxCount 1 ;
        sh:message """The ontology does not specify exactly one date of creation. 
        The date must be given in xsd:dateTime format.
        Recommended property: <https://purl.org/dc/terms/created>
        Example statement (text/turtle): <https://www.purl.org/SomeOntology> dcterms:created "2020-11-19T00:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .
        """@en ;
        sh:description "This shape checks whether the ontology provides its creation date. It produces a warning message if not."@en ;
        sh:name "Creation date"@en ;
    ] ;

    sh:property [
        sh:path [sh:alternativePath (dcterms:created schema:dateCreated pav:createdOn prov:generatedAtTime )] ;
        sh:severity sh:Info ;
        sh:datatype xsd:dateTime ;
        sh:message """The ontology does not specify its date of creation in xsd:dateTime format.
        Recommended property: <https://purl.org/dc/terms/created>
        Example statement (text/turtle): <https://www.purl.org/SomeOntology> dcterms:created "2020-11-19T00:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .
        """@en ; 
        sh:description "This shape checks whether the ontology provides its creation date in xsd:dateTime format. It produces an info message if not."@en ;
        sh:name "Creation date datatype"@en ; 
    ] ;

